.TH PLWID 3plplot  "May, 2005" "" "PLplot API"
.SH NAME
\fBplwid\fP - Set pen width 
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBplwid\fP(\fIwidth\fP)
.SH DESCRIPTION

.P
Sets the pen width. 
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIwidth\fP (PLINT, input) 
The desired pen width.  If \fIwidth\fP is negative or the same as the previous value no action is taken.
\fIwidth\fP = 0 should be interpreted as
as the minimum valid pen width for the device.  The interpretation of positive
\fIwidth\fP values is also device
dependent. 

